#### **Slide 4 â†’ [Protocol Page 3: Dataset]**  
**Data Source & Ethics**  
> - **Fully synthetic / simulated dataset**  
> - Mimics real verification behavior **without real identities**  
> - **No Aadhaar numbers, biometrics, names, or PII**

#### **Slide 5 â†’ [Protocol Page 3: Data Governance]**  
**Privacy by Design**  
> - Restricted columns (`aadhaar_number`, `phone`, etc.) **explicitly removed**  
> - Follows **data minimization** and **anonymization**  
> - Compliant with **Aadhaar Act Section 29** principles

#### **Slide 6 â†’ [Protocol Page 4: Methodology]**  
**End-to-End Pipeline**  
> 1. Ingest synthetic CSV  
> 2. Clean: `fillna()`, `drop_duplicates()`  
> 3. Secure: Remove restricted fields  
> 4. Prepare: Select only governance-relevant features

#### **Slide 7 â†’ [Protocol Page 4: Processing Proof]**  
**Pandas for Transparency**  
> ```python
> df.fillna(method='ffill', inplace=True)
> df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)
> df = df[['verification_type', 'region_code', 'auth_result']]
> ```  
> â†’ Every step is **traceable, auditable, and repeatable**

